{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014VAgSU3HK3FdazdvVPwFdA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is exactly where the phantom creation happens. When `parseRalphMessage` matches a pattern inside JSON, `handleAgentEvent` calls `updateStoryStatus(event.key, 'review')` with a key like `1-1-foo`. With my fix to `parseRalphMessage` (skip JSON lines), the phantom event won't fire. And with my fix to `updateStoryStatus` (reject unknown keys), even if it does fire, it returns a fail result which is already logged as a warning. The code already handles the failure gracefully.\n\nNow let me build and run tests."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":618,"cache_read_input_tokens":77563,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":618},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2a44c687-0795-47af-a7f4-46576056f827","uuid":"127621de-815d-4f57-9b92-694b16a14fc7"}
