spective вЂ” do not ignore them.\n\nCRITICAL: Run `codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCRITICAL: The session issues log contains `## Token Report` sections from each subagent. Aggregate these to understand WHERE tokens were spent inside subagents (not just the parent). Look for:\n- Which subagent phases had the most tool calls?\n- Which subagents read the same files repeatedly?\n- Which Bash commands produced the largest outputs?\n- What redundant operations were reported?\nInclude this subagent-level breakdown in the cost analysis section.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** вЂ” which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** вЂ” categorize and analyze all issues from the session log:\n   - Bugs discovered during implementation or verification\n   - Workarounds applied (tech debt introduced this session)\n   - Code quality concerns raised by reviewers\n   - Verification gaps (escalated ACs, weak evidence)\n   - Tooling/infrastructure problems (sandbox, permissions, CLI issues)\n3. **Cost analysis** вЂ” from the cost report:\n   - Total API-equivalent cost this sprint\n   - Cost per phase (which phases are most expensive?)\n   - Cost per story (which stories cost the most and why?)\n   - Wasted spend (no-op sessions, failed verifications, retries)\n   - Cost optimization opportunities\n4. **What went well** вЂ” stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n5. **What went wrong** вЂ” failures, blockers, stuck stories, wasted iterations\n6. **Lessons learned** вЂ” patterns to repeat or avoid\n7. **Action items** вЂ” concrete next steps\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md.\n\nSince a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions вЂ” proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"a6d9e9b6d15584793","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md`.\n\n**Summary of findings:**\n\n- **Sessions 16-22 covered.** Only 2 of 7 sessions were productive (21: root cause identification, 22: root cause fix). Sessions 16-17, 19-20 were identical no-op state corrections.\n- **Root cause fixed:** `parseRalphMessage()` was matching story patterns inside JSON lines, and `updateStoryStatus()` was silently creating unknown story entries. Both patched in session 22.\n- **Total project cost: $661.66** (+$21.88 since last retro). Verification phase is 55% of all spend. Estimated $20-25 wasted on 12 redundant state correction sessions.\n- **Residual issue:** Phantom `1-1-foo` still exists in sprint-state.json (total=75, should be 74). Needs cleanup.\n- **9 action items** tracked, 2 marked done (the root cause fixes), 2 new (cleanup phantom, add integration test)."}],"totalDurationMs":109924,"totalTokens":37159,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3378,"cache_read_input_tokens":33498,"output_tokens":282,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3378},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
